# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __imod__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__imod__')
#
# All 10 asyncio classes return false for __imod__.
# In-place modulo (__imod__, %=) is the augmented assignment variant of __mod__.
# asyncio types define no __mod__ (wave 659), so __imod__ is equally absent.
# Note: str defines __mod__ for % string formatting, but asyncio types are not
#   str subclasses and implement no such formatting protocol.
# asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition/Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: synchronization
#   primitives with no in-place modulo semantics of any kind.
# asyncio.Task/Future: coroutine result handles; %= is not defined.
# asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: queue types manage items through
#   put()/get() coroutine calls only — no __imod__ is defined.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

